  [Fabulous Family Fun!](https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g46528-d28191159-r1059617394-Savannah_Sunset_Resort_Spa-Jackson_New_Jersey.html)
  
  We went to this resort for my nephew’s birthday and my husband’s birthday and we had an amazing time! The customer service was excellent from start to finish, the glamping family suite was very nice, and the dinner at the Lodge was delicious. My nephew got the New York strip steak and he said it was “the juiciest steak ever!” We enjoyed listening to the live music during and after dinner and playing cornhole. I think our favorite part was feeding the giraffes in the morning after breakfast (which was included). From our room, we were able to see some of the Safari animals, but if you really want to see them from your room, get a suite with a large deck overlooking the safari. We were able to hop on the Safari truck after checking out and then go to the amusement park. I suggest going off peak season because the lines were not bad at all.
  
